When I began my partnership with @onlyfans I definitely received some strong feedback. I never took any of it personally because I know just as much as the next person what OF is primarily used for, but that’s not what I use it for.  I want to be completely transparent discussing this topic because I have lots of young fans, followers, a DAUGHTER, family etc who deserve to know why I joined the platform. So let’s dive in.⁣

OnlyFans was originally created to connect and engage with all walks of life and primarily a way to engage and connect with athletes, celebs, artists, musicians etc. Over the pandemic it’s no secret how the platform drastically changed. That being said I know that OF has big plans to pivot and I wanted to be part of that and bring new eyes to the platform in the process.⁣
⁣
I want to make it very clear that I in no way shape or form offer nude or explicit content. My OF content revolves around ME and my life- depicting my day to day as a mom, fighter, and influencer. I have very strong moral boundaries in which I intend to uphold…(Let me just say that I have no judgment towards anyone who expresses themselves as they wish…it’s really none of my business)... ⁣
And yes, I show my sexy side for sure! Embracing who you are is so beautiful and empowering- I think it's vital for women to feel sexy and happy in their skin, so yes I do offer content of that nature. ⁣

Yes the monetary aspect is nice, but to feel accepted, lifted and loved from so many people just feels awesome. It’s only going to be better from here!⁣
⁣
If you are already a fan, THANK YOU! If not, I invite you to come see for yourself. Come be part of the side of my journey I don’t always share publicly on the other platforms. Did I mention it's FREE?! ⁣
See you on the inside, love you!⁣ 🫶

There’s a growing opportunity in literally everything. So that’s what I’m choosing- to grow and get stronger. 

I look forward to seeing myself 100% healthy and at my very best.

I’ll never have all the answers. I’ll never understand why when it seems like I’m finally gaining momentum that the rug is suddenly pulled from under me. 
But I do know how strong I am and all I have overcome- I can’t help but believe I will only be stronger for it. There’s a lesson and growth opportunities in everything, so I just have to trust the process and keep pressing forward. 

I’m so thankful for those around me who exude positive energy. I’m thankful I don’t have to endure another surgery… thankful for the highs and lows because it has shaped me in ways that I can’t even explain. Thankful I can wake up another day and use my legs- even though painful at times. 
But we all have a choice right? How we choose to show up. How we choose to look at our situation and react… it’s all choices. Sounds simple because it is.. some people will say otherwise because they make a simple choice to see the negative instead of the positive. 
(don’t get it twisted- the journey is fucking hard and it never gets easier.)

The power of choice is there for the taking… for all us. 
We are never powerless or defined by our circumstances. We are shaped by them and how we pick ourselves back up because honestly the hardships are designed to make us stronger not the opposite.
Just remember next time when life fucks with you… don’t give in, run from it or accept it - step towards it and reclaim what’s yours.

My daughter and I fled to a n emergency domestic violence safe haven (@womenagainstabuse) and we lived there for 4 months. ⁣
⁣
Sometimes you have to lose it all to gain everything and more. ⁣
⁣
I was given a second chance and an opportunity to rebuild my life on MY TERMS. I went to war for myself and never gave up- even on the hardest days. ⁣
⁣
I dug deep and rediscovered myself through self love. Not only did I survive but I am now a former MMA Champion, teacher, speaker and advocate. I turned my story into a powerful message of over coming adversity through self love, grit and the power of positivity. ⁣
⁣
It’s amazing what you can accomplish when you believe in yourself and refuse to let your circumstances define you. I am defined by how I chose myself and my daughter. By how I picked myself back up and by how I choose to be a beacon for others to spread hope and love. ⁣
⁣
Be your own hero! ⁣

Story time! 

As you may already know, I tore my meniscus one week out before my fight back in March. Unfortunately that resulted in pulling out of the fight. 

Luckily, no surgery was required so my coaches and I made a solid plan moving forward to get healthy and get back in the cage later this year. 

I travelled to VA to get Infinity Matrix regenerative therapy (stems cells) from my sponsor @newhoperegeneration. 

10 days later I started my pt program curated by my strength coach @coach.mikecsp . I was absolutely killing it! 💪💪

Fast forward to a couple of weeks ago when I was on the back end of my rehab, I had a training accident which resulted in setting me back to day 1 😫. I was in a lot of pain and was back on crutches because I couldn’t walk. 
I told myself I’d give it a full week of staying off it and focusing only on recovery and to allow the cells to do their thing and then make the decision to see my orthopedic if I didn’t see an improvements from that. 

At the one week mark I was not feeling much pain and was able to walk with my brace and from@there was seeing and feeling daily improvements. 

Yesterday was my first day back on my pt and I felt great. I’m so happy I have my body the chance to work with the cells and avoid another surgery. I couldn’t be happier. 

It’s easy to get depressed when you incur one injury after the next, facing set back after set back. But what I’ve learned most in my over 5 years of knee injuries is that you have to give yourself grace and focus on moving forward. Injuries happen so it’s better to just accept it and keep your sights on  how you can resolve it and get healthy. That’s it. Sure it sucks and takes time out of what you’d actually be doing but the long term results should always be at the forefront .  Focus on setting your health up for success for LONGEVITY and QUALITY of life,  not limiting yourself to just one segment like a completion or whatever the case maybe. Yes, always set goals but always look at it as a whole. 

Thank you @newhoperegeneration for setting me on this path of long term health and recovery. It ain’t always pretty but I am most confident in my body to get through this injury.

People ask me ALL the time about my ethnicity and embarrassingly enough I never  fully knew the answer to that question. SO, I finally dove in and took a DNA test with @ancestry to find out where my bloodline comes from. ⁣
⁣
Over the last 10 + years my family has been diving deep into our family history because parts of it is truly interesting. From what we knew about my mom’s background was that she isFrench, Italian, Lithuanian, Scottish and Irish. My dad is African but learned later that he has a high percentage of Scottish and Irish as well (who knew?!) ⁣
⁣
We always took a lot of pride in our Italian roots, so much so that my family started a fresh pasta production company and bakery located in Cincinnati @findlaymarket @bouchards_bakery_and_pasta family@owned and operated for 15 years! (Fun fact 😉)
⁣
Even though my Pops (my great great grandfather) was 100% Sicilian, I have ZERO Italian in my DNA which is actually a tough pill to swallow. But I don’t care, I will always be Italian 😂 🇮🇹 ⁣
What I did find out was pretty awesome though- check out my results below 👇 ⁣
⁣
34% African ( Nigeria, Mali, Ghana, Benin, Togo, Cameroon, Congo, Western Bantu Peoples) ⁣
⁣
17% French 🇫🇷 ⁣
⁣
14% Scottish 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 ⁣
⁣
9% Irish 🇮🇪 ⁣
⁣
Additionally: English, Western Europe, Baltics (Lithuania), Philippines, Indigenous Americas ( both northern and Yucatán Peninsula), Russia and Wales. ⁣
⁣
I am really excited to learn more about where I come from and begin to integrate more cultural experiences into mine and my daughters lives. She too is a mix of so many incredible ethnicities as well and I want to honor that by recognizing all that she is! ⁣
I think it’s important for all of us to know where our bloodlines comes from because it opens up so many doors to learning and meeting family we never knew existed. ⁣

Life is such a cool journey! ⁣

Nearly one year ago, I made one of the  most important speeches of my life. And while all of my speeches and opportunities to share my story are important, this one in particular was a full circle moment. ⁣
⁣
Most people consider me a success story or hold me to a higher standard, but the truth is I’m no different. I am no different than the next person who might experience tragedy, hardship, and tribulations. ⁣
⁣
The only reason why I am here today and able to speak on my experiences is because I made a decision. I did what was necessary to pick myself back up, but I didn’t see the broken pieces as something that wasn’t mendable. When my life shattered into a thousand different fragments, I saw it as a thousand ways to rebuild- MY WAY. My new  foundation was built on self- love, resilience, strength, power, and hope. From there I built a fortress! Protected by ME- this amazing person I created. I am my own hero. ⁣
⁣
After surviving the hardest thing I ever endured, I knew I had a purpose. For the last 5 years it has been my mission to raise awareness and to help others overcome similar circumstances. It’s my mission to help people realize that our circumstances are temporary and no matter how hard it gets, we have to be no matter what people. To say “no matter what, I will get through this”...whatever it is. To understand that weathering the storm doesn’t mean that you are defined by the destruction it left behind. It’s a second chance to learn, rebuild, and grow...all on your terms.⁣
⁣
When I had the honor of being the Survivor Speaker at the biggest press conference of the year, for the very organization who saved my life….that was the full circle moment. One that has truly defined me.⁣
